{"build_type":"tool","description":"One-directory listing tool (the depth-0 complete answer — NOT a lossy depth/limit knob; it is the full contents of exactly ONE directory, the missing precondition that makes navigate-by-path usable). Request (argv[1]): {\"list-directory-entries-with-metadata\": {\"path\": \"<dir>\"}}. Returns {root, entries:[{type,name,size_bytes?,permissions?,symlink_target?,modified_unix?}, …]}: every entry of that one directory (NON-RECURSIVE), sorted by name, with type, file size, default-encoded permission deviations, and resolved types plus symlink targets. Owns its own failure via a DETERMINISTIC ROW BUDGET (default_directory_listing_row_budget): if the directory has more entries than the budget, it emits the rows up to the budget plus truncated:1 + a hint to narrow the path or use the relevance tool — a LOUD structured signal, never a 120s black-box. Bad request (no argv / unparseable / no arg object / no path) -> clean JSON {error}, never crashes. Reuses parse_argument_vector_json_request, locate_named_member_inside_mapping, default_directory_listing_row_budget, begin_empty_sequence_document_value, list_directory_entries_with_type, emit_directory_rows_with_metadata, begin_empty_mapping_document_value, add_str_field, add_number_to_object, attach_named_member_inside_mapping, emit_result_object_onto_standard_output.","module_name":"enumerate-directory-entries-bearing-metadata-records","package_name":"enumerate-directory-entries-bearing-metadata-records","function_definitions":{"enumerate-directory-entries-bearing-metadata-records":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"input","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_ty